The paper discusses a new approach to reinforcement learning that combines the benefits of model-free and model-based methods. It focuses on training goal-conditioned value functions using temporal difference models (TDMs) and applies them to continuous control tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
